11#ifndef VIDEO_BUFFERED_FRAME_DECRYPTOR_H_
12#define VIDEO_BUFFERED_FRAME_DECRYPTOR_H_
13
14#include <deque>
15#include <memory>
16
17#include "api/crypto/crypto_options.h"
18#include "api/crypto/frame_decryptor_interface.h"
19#include "modules/video_coding/frame_object.h"
20
21namespace webrtc {
22
23// This callback is provided during the construction of the
24// BufferedFrameDecryptor and is called each time a frame is sucessfully
25// decrypted by the buffer.
26class OnDecryptedFrameCallback {
27 public:
28 virtual ~OnDecryptedFrameCallback() = default;
29 // Called each time a decrypted frame is returned.
30 virtual void OnDecryptedFrame(std::unique_ptr<RtpFrameObject> frame) = 0;
31};
32
33// This callback is called each time there is a status change in the decryption
34// stream. For example going from a none state to a first decryption or going
35// frome a decryptable state to a non decryptable state.
36class OnDecryptionStatusChangeCallback {
37 public:
38 virtual ~OnDecryptionStatusChangeCallback() = default;
39 // Called each time the decryption stream status changes. This call is
40 // blocking so the caller must relinquish the callback quickly. This status
41 // must match what is specified in the FrameDecryptorInterface file. Notably
42 // 0 must indicate success and any positive integer is a failure.
43 virtual void OnDecryptionStatusChange(
44 FrameDecryptorInterface::Status status) = 0;
45};
46
47// The BufferedFrameDecryptor is responsible for deciding when to pass
48// decrypted received frames onto the OnDecryptedFrameCallback. Frames can be
49// delayed when frame encryption is enabled but the key hasn't arrived yet. In
50// this case we stash about 1 second of encrypted frames instead of dropping
51// them to prevent re-requesting the key frame. This optimization is
52// particularly important on low bandwidth networks. Note stashing is only ever
53// done if we have never sucessfully decrypted a frame before. After the first
54// successful decryption payloads will never be stashed.
55class BufferedFrameDecryptor final {
56 public:
57 // Constructs a new BufferedFrameDecryptor that can hold
58 explicit BufferedFrameDecryptor(
59 OnDecryptedFrameCallback* decrypted_frame_callback,
60 OnDecryptionStatusChangeCallback* decryption_status_change_callback);
61 ~BufferedFrameDecryptor();
62 // This object cannot be copied.
63 BufferedFrameDecryptor(const BufferedFrameDecryptor&) = delete;
64 BufferedFrameDecryptor& operator=(const BufferedFrameDecryptor&) = delete;
65
66 // Sets a new frame decryptor as the decryptor for the buffered frame
67 // decryptor. This allows the decryptor to be switched out without resetting
68 // the video stream.
69 void SetFrameDecryptor(
70 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameDecryptorInterface> frame_decryptor);
71
72 // Determines whether the frame should be stashed, dropped or handed off to
73 // the OnDecryptedFrameCallback.
74 void ManageEncryptedFrame(std::unique_ptr<RtpFrameObject> encrypted_frame);
75
76 private:
77 // Represents what should be done with a given frame.
78 enum class FrameDecision { kStash, kDecrypted, kDrop };
79
80 // Attempts to decrypt the frame, if it fails and no prior frames have been
81 // decrypted it will return kStash. Otherwise fail to decrypts will return
82 // kDrop. Successful decryptions will always return kDecrypted.
83 FrameDecision DecryptFrame(RtpFrameObject* frame);
84 // Retries all the stashed frames this is triggered each time a kDecrypted
85 // event occurs.
86 void RetryStashedFrames();
87
88 static const size_t kMaxStashedFrames = 24;
89
90 const bool generic_descriptor_auth_experiment_;
91 bool first_frame_decrypted_ = false;
92 FrameDecryptorInterface::Status last_status_ =
93 FrameDecryptorInterface::Status::kUnknown;
94 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameDecryptorInterface> frame_decryptor_;
95 OnDecryptedFrameCallback* const decrypted_frame_callback_;
96 OnDecryptionStatusChangeCallback* const decryption_status_change_callback_;
97 std::deque<std::unique_ptr<RtpFrameObject>> stashed_frames_;
98};
99
100} // namespace webrtc
101
102#endif // VIDEO_BUFFERED_FRAME_DECRYPTOR_H_
